03/09/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- NATO South Wing Commander US Admiral Harry Ulrich met with Macedonian Defence Minister Lazar Elenovski and Army Chief of Staff Major General Miroslav Stojanovski on Friday (1 September) in Skopje.
Talks focused on Macedonia's defence reforms and the country's participation in NATO missions.
Ulrich praised the country's progress in reforms, the logistic assistance that the army provides to KFOR and the participation of their members in NATO's missions.
(MIA, Macedonian government website - 01/09/06)
